The Otun of Owu Muslims, Alhaji Rasaki Atanda Sanusi, is dead. The late Alhaji Sanusi, who is the father of former Managing Director of Lagos Sate Signage and Advertisement Agency (LASAA), Mr. Mobolaji Sanusi, died on Monday at 92. He has since been buried according to Islamic rites. His 8th day firdaus prayer comes up on Monday February 7, at No 10, NTA Road, Totoro, Abeokuta by 11.30am prompt. Alhaji Sanusi retired as Director at the Ogun State Printing Corporation, formerly called Government Press, in 1989. He was born on March 9, 1930 to the family of Alhaji Olabaji Sanusi Akogun Compound, Owu, Abeokuta. A staunch Muslim during his life time, Alhaji Rasaki Sanusi is survived by six children and several grandchildren amongst whom are Abiodun Sanusi, Omotayo Ayanjimi, Asisat Oyedokun, Omotunde Lawal, Odunayo Iriemi and Mobolaji Sanusi, immediate past MD/CEO of LASAA.